values: ...leave a comment and let me know.  I might just post on here if I believe someone might read it.

You Are The Champion
"Don't worry, I got it."

You play as the Hero. You are the one who usually tries to take on the world for any cause you believe in. You are a natural leader in most circles and are not afraid to take that position if a situation calls for it. Others look to you for inspiration and praise you for your acheivements. Even though they love and adore you, however, you are left feeling alone or overwhelmed many times. You're almost always positive and keep your chin up despite any setbacks because you know that you will succeed in the end, no matter how long it takes.

Which Classic Story Role Do You Play?
brought to you by Quizilla
Kinda scary considering Katy's results. Oh well, quizzes aren't everything. -J PS - I just read about Katy's change in employment (to none) and WHOA!!! I'm calling her right now.

Have I ever mentioned to the 3 total people that read this thing that I LOVE music?

Doves - Black and White Town

Anyone who has digital cable also has access to lots of free stuff through ON DEMAND. I have been watching music videos and I was reminded of how great codeseven is. And I was also reminded of how creepy giant bunnies are. In addition to that I was reminded that I don't get nearly enough readers on either of my blog deals. It's unfortunate, but I suppose that's the way of these things when you don't have a lot of friends that are ubergeeks. I guess this thing's still less than 2 months old too. I don't know, I just want to feel like there's a purpose to what I'm doing. If I was writing about my problems or whatever it wouldn't matter if people read it or not. But I'm trying to spread some sweet-ass news, and I want to get other people excited about this stuff. Well, congratulations livejournal, you've managed to pull out even more complaints from my mind. So for those who read this and are potentially unknown to me, you should check out this better blog if you haven't yet. I don't update that often, but I try. And please, if you have any response at all to anything, go ahead and post. Hey, even the new pope has commented on one of my stories on the other blog. Thanks to all those who read anything I write. And as always, I hope at least a couple people find something useful.

-J

Today is the last of a long series of days working at Bistro Wasabi. Starting tomorrow I'll be enjoying THREE DAYS OFF!!! Apparently before work today I have a lot of things to do around the house, including moving boxes of my stuff, setting up my mom's computer, and putting more doorknobs on. You can see pictures of the large device I found in my yard at my real blog.  Right now I'm watching "Attack of the Show" and this guy is on who made a little movie about Mario getting killed.  He just said that moms were calling in complaining that their children were devastated because their hero was dead.  Check out his movies here.  Well, it's off to work with me.  I'm going to teach my mom how to match the colors and the back of her computer to make it work.

All moved in.  Check my real blog in a couple days for some pictures.  I swear this is the "tired house."  Always, without fail, at 9pm every member of my family begins to fall asleep.  It's very sad.  Also, I don't know if my room will ever be right.  There's so much stuff I just can't believe it.  I need two rooms still.  Now I start a long period of working every five seconds.  

Wed - work, Thu - liquor serving class, Fri - work, Sat - work, Sun - work, Mon - off, Tue - work, Wed - work.  

Wow....just seeing it all like that makes me tired and sore.  I pity my poor, abused feet.  I soooooo wish I could finish watching Wolf's Rain soon.  Right now it's time for some Xenosaga so I can go to bed a little later and not be a total loser.  You know, I really kind of have to stay up late.  If I go to bed at 9pm one night, and then work until 10:30pm the next night, don't you think I'll just shut down at work?  I don't know.  All I know is that I have got to force myself to stay asleep later than 7:15am.  No alarm or anything, that's when I've been waking up.  Does this livejournal business force you into complaining or something?  I think there are greater powers at work behind this webservice.  I am very suspicious.

Most of the painting is done, the music is complete, the type-text is purchased, but the script isn't yet complete.  Oh, and I learned how to install doorknobs today.  Too bad it can't all have been done yesterday.  I do so want to move into the new house and finally be able to get on with life.

Good luck, be strong, don't relent.
Well, not really.  Good luck getting a lot of updates on this thing.  Basically this just gets me an in to some important information.  Take that SUCKAHS!!!!
